('Metformin', 'Diabetes', 'Metformin is the first-line oral medication for type 2 diabetes. It reduces hepatic glucose production and improves insulin sensitivity.', '500-1000mg twice daily, max 2550mg, extended release once daily', 'GI upset, nausea, diarrhea, lactic acidosis, vitamin B12 deficiency', 4.8, '$$', 'Prescription only', 'Bristol-Myers Squibb', 'Biguanide', 'B', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '1.5-5 hours', '1-2 hours', '12-24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 9876, 'Contrast media,Insulin,Sulfonylureas,Cimetidine', 'Lactic acidosis, renal impairment, GI upset', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Insulin Glargine', 'Diabetes', 'Insulin glargine is a long-acting insulin analog used for diabetes management. It provides a steady basal insulin level for 24 hours.', '10-40 units once daily, dose individualized', 'Hypoglycemia, weight gain, lipodystrophy, injection site reactions', 4.8, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Sanofi', 'Long-acting Insulin', 'C', 'Refrigerate 2-8°C', '12-24 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 8765, 'Sulfonylureas,Pioglitazone,Salicylates,Alcohol', 'Hypoglycemia, weight gain, injection site reactions', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Insulin Lispro', 'Diabetes', 'Insulin lispro is a rapid-acting insulin analog used for diabetes management. It has a rapid onset and short duration for prandial coverage.', 'Dose individualized, 0.5-1 unit/kg/day, taken before meals', 'Hypoglycemia, weight gain, lipodystrophy, injection site reactions', 4.7, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Eli Lilly', 'Rapid-acting Insulin', 'C', 'Refrigerate 2-8°C', '1-2 hours', '15-30 min', '3-5 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 7654, 'Sulfonylureas,Pioglitazone,Salicylates,Alcohol', 'Hypoglycemia, weight gain, injection site reactions', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
