('Cabergoline', 'Endocrine', 'Cabergoline is a dopamine agonist used for hyperprolactinemia. It inhibits prolactin secretion with once weekly dosing.', '0.25-0.5mg twice weekly, max 1mg weekly', 'Nausea, dizziness, headache, orthostatic hypotension, constipation, fatigue', 4.5, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Dopamine Agonist', 'B', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '65 hours', '1-2 hours', '7 days', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 4567, 'Antihypertensives,Antipsychotics,MAOIs,Alcohol', 'Orthostatic hypotension, cardiac valvulopathy, pulmonary fibrosis', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Calcitonin', 'Endocrine', 'Calcitonin is a hormone used for Paget\'s disease, hypercalcemia, and postmenopausal osteoporosis. It inhibits osteoclast activity.', '50-100 units daily SQ/IM, 200 units nasal spray daily', 'Nausea, flushing, injection site reaction, nasal irritation, hypocalcemia', 4.3, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Novartis', 'Calcitonin', 'C', 'Refrigerate 2-8°C', '2-3 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, 'Calcium,Calcitriol,Antacids,Digoxin', 'Hypocalcemia, allergy, monitor calcium levels', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Cinacalcet', 'Endocrine', 'Cinacalcet is a calcimimetic used for hyperparathyroidism and hypercalcemia. It increases calcium sensing receptor sensitivity.', '30-60mg once daily, titrate to 120mg daily', 'Nausea, vomiting, hypocalcemia, GI upset, headache, dizziness', 4.4, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Amgen', 'Calcimimetic', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '30-40 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, 'CYP3A4 inhibitors,CYP2D6 inhibitors,Strong CYP3A4 inhibitors', 'Hypocalcemia, monitor calcium, nausea, drug interactions', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
