('Isosorbide Mononitrate', 'Cardiovascular', 'Isosorbide mononitrate is a nitrate used for angina prophylaxis. It is a vasodilator that reduces myocardial oxygen demand.', '20-40mg twice daily, extended release 60-120mg once daily', 'Headache, hypotension, dizziness, flushing, reflex tachycardia', 4.4, '$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Nitrate', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '4-6 hours', '1-2 hours', '8-12 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 3456, 'Sildenafil,Tadalafil,Vardenafil,Alcohol,Antihypertensives', 'Hypotension, tolerance, interaction with PDE5 inhibitors', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
