('Misoprostol', 'Gastrointestinal', 'Misoprostol is a prostaglandin analog used for ulcer prevention in NSAID users. It protects the gastric mucosa and reduces acid secretion.', '100-200mcg 4 times daily', 'Diarrhea, abdominal pain, nausea, uterine contractions, miscarriage', 4.2, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Prostaglandin Analog', 'X', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '20-30 min', '30-60 min', '4-6 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, 'NSAIDs,Antacids,Antidiarrheals', 'Diarrhea, uterine contractions, pregnancy category X, not for pregnant women', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
