('Primidone', 'Nervous System', 'Primidone is an anticonvulsant used for seizure disorders. It is metabolized to phenobarbital and phenylethylmalonamide.', '50-250mg 3-4 times daily, max 2g', 'Dizziness, ataxia, sedation, nystagmus, GI upset, hepatotoxicity', 4.2, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Anticonvulsant', 'D', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '10-12 hours', '1-2 hours', '6-8 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, 'Warfarin,Valproate,Antiepileptics,Antifungals', 'Sedation, hepatotoxicity, drug interactions, slow titration', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
